 Key Design Decisions

 1. Buffer overflow → force consolidation (default). 20 accumulated mundane facts are collectively worth encoding.
 2. Pre-sleep always flushes buffer. Sleep is the natural consolidation boundary — you don't lose memories right before falling
 asleep.
 3. Crash loses buffer (by design). No disk persistence = true retrograde amnesia.
 4. Surprise on corrections even without new facts. "Actually, I moved to Berlin" may not extract as a new triple if "lives in X"
 already exists, but the correction marker still fires surprise → consolidates pending buffer.
 5. Backward compatible. consolidation_moment.enabled: false restores exact per-turn injection behavior.

